{{family name hatnote|Alonso|Mujica|lang=Spanish}}
'''Júnior Osmar Ignacio Alonso Mujica''' (born 9 February 1993) is a Paraguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] or [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

==Club career==
===Lille===
Alonso joined French club [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in a permanent transfer in January 2017.<ref name="Lille">{{cite web|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2018/official-lille-central-defender-junior-alonso-joins-celta-vigo-on-loan/|title=Official: Lille central defender Junior Alonso joins Celta Vigo on loan|publisher=Get Football News|access-date=25 July 2019}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 18 February 2017, coming on as a second-half substitute in a win over [[Stade Malherbe Caen|SM Caen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/paraguayos-junior-alonso-debuto-en-el-lille-de-francia|title=El esperado debut|trans-title=The long-awaited debut|publisher=Tigo Sports|date=18 February 2017|access-date=25 July 2019|language=es|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726005850/http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/paraguayos-junior-alonso-debuto-en-el-lille-de-francia|archive-date=26 July 2019}}</ref> He would go on to make 56 appearances for Lille in all competitions before leaving on loan in August 2018.<ref name="Lille"/>

====Celta (loan)====
On 14 August 2018, Alonso was loaned to [[La Liga]]'s [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] for one year with an option to make the deal permanent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2018/08/14/primera/1534268179_721458.html|title=Junior Alonso ya es del Celta|publisher=AS|language=es|date=14 August 2018|access-date=29 July 2024}}</ref><ref name="Lille"/>

====Boca Juniors (loan)====
On 2 January 2019, he was loaned to [[Boca Juniors]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-lille-prete-junior-alonso-a-boca-juniors/973440|title=Transferts: Lille prête Junior Alonso à Boca Juniors|newspaper=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|date=2 January 2019|access-date=29 July 2024}}</ref> On 2 May 2019, Alonso was an unused substitute as Boca defeated [[Rosario Central]] in the [[2018 Supercopa Argentina]] on penalty-kicks after the match ended 0–0.<ref name="Supercopa">{{cite news|url=https://www.foxsports.com.ar/news/406248-alfaro-lo-quiero-compartir-con-guillermo|title=Alfaro: "Lo quiero compartir con Guillermo"|date=2 May 2019|agency=Fox Sports|language=es|access-date=3 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503035923/https://www.foxsports.com.ar/news/406248-alfaro-lo-quiero-compartir-con-guillermo|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Atlético Mineiro===
On 2 July 2020, Alonso joined Brazilian club [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] on a four-year deal for a [[Euro|€]]3 million fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/atletico-mg/noticia/atletico-mg-anuncia-contratacao-do-zagueiro-junior-alonso-que-pertencia-ao-lille.ghtml|title=Atlético-MG anuncia contratação do zagueiro Junior Alonso, que pertencia ao Lille|date=2 July 2020|publisher=Globoesporte|language=pt-br|access-date=29 July 2024}}</ref> 
He quickly became a starter on the team, and in 2021 he was champion of [[2021 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] and [[2021 Copa do Brasil]], playing in 51 matches and scoring 1 goal, being captain and a pillar of defense.

===Krasnodar===
On 7 January 2022, Russian club [[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]] announced that the terms of transfer has been agreed with Atlético Mineiro, and the terms of the 3.5-year contract has been agreed with Alonso.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]]|url=https://fckrasnodar.ru/team/news/object/?object_id=141015|title="Краснодар" И "АтлетикО Минейро" Согласовали Трансфер Хуниора Алонсо|date=7 January 2022|language=ru|access-date=29 July 2024}}</ref> The contract was signed on 12 January 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]]|url=https://www.fckrasnodar.ru/team/news/object/?object_id=141039|title=Хуниор Алонсо Стал Игроком "Краснодара"|date=12 January 2022|access-date=13 January 2022|language=ru}}</ref> On 3 March 2022, following the [[2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine|Russian invasion of Ukraine]], Krasnodar announced that his contract was suspended and he would not train with the team, but the contract was not terminated and remained valid.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=[[FC Krasnodar]]|url=https://fckrasnodar.ru/team/news/object/?object_id=141382|title="Краснодар" Приостановил Контраты С НесколЬкими Игроками|date=3 March 2022|access-date=3 March 2022|lang=ru|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303143559/https://fckrasnodar.ru/team/news/object/?object_id=141382|archive-date=3 March 2022|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====Return to Atlético Mineiro (loan)====
On 14 March 2022, Atlético Mineiro announced the return of Alonso on loan until the end of 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atletico.com.br/tem-novidade-na-area/|title=Tem novidade na área|date=14 March 2022|publisher=Clube Atlético Mineiro|language=pt-br|access-date=29 July 2024}}</ref>

===Second return to Atlético Mineiro===
On 10 July 2024, Alonso rejoined [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] on a two-and-a-half-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atletico.com.br/junior-alonso-esta-de-volta-ao-galo/|title=Junior Alonso está de volta ao Galo!|date=10 July 2024|publisher=Clube Atlético Mineiro|language=pt-br|access-date=29 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Alonso is a full international for [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]], having made his senior debut for his country in 2013.<ref name="Lille"/>

In a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] match on 23 March 2017, Alonso scored the winning goal, and his first for the national team, in a 2–1 defeat of [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/paraguay-vs-ecuador/349959|title=Paraguay 2:1 Ecuador|date=23 March 2017|access-date=25 July 2019|publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref>

On 29 May 2019, Alonso was selected to the final 23-man roster for the [[2019 Copa América]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.apf.org.py/n/la-lista-definitiva-23-de-la-albirroja-para-la-copa-america-brasil-2019|title=La lista definitiva (23) de la Albirroja para la Copa América "Brasil 2019"|language=es|website=apf.org.py|publisher=APF|date=29 May 2019|access-date=29 July 2024|archive-date=1 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801055809/https://www.apf.org.py/n/la-lista-definitiva-23-de-la-albirroja-para-la-copa-america-brasil-2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> He would go on to start in all four of Paraguay's matches, playing every single minute, as they lost in the quarter-finals in a penalty shoot-out to hosts and eventual champions [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=547350|title=Brazil survive penalty shootout to beat Paraguay|publisher=ESPN|date=27 June 2019|access-date=25 July 2019}}</ref>

